original: HAGNE, Carl Adolf Seth, Direktör, Göteborg, f V Frölunda, Gbg o Boh län, 7/1 91 av hemm.äg A Johanson o Johanna Andersson, gm Birgitta Lundgren. V:a Realsk Gbg, hdlsinst. Hdlsbitr fma Frans Lundin Gbg 10, d:o fma Gulin, Weidenborg & Co 11—15. Dir i eget företag, AB Hagne, Weidenborg & Co Gbg sed. dess start 16. Komp Weidenborg uttr ur fman 35, sonen Herbert Hagne intr ss medarb 43. Styr.led o kassör i Frn Gbgs Herrekiperingar. Resor: Norge, Danm, Engl, Tyskl, Frankr 23—32. Inneh Sv :es Köpm.-frbs ftjt g. Tillh Göta Coldin, W6, Bowl.kl 3:an Gbg mfl idr.sam.slutn o klubbar. Hobbies: Idrott, alla slag.
translated: HAGNE, Carl Adolf Seth, Director, Gothenburg, born in Frölunda, Gothenburg and Bohus County, on January 7, 1891, to home owners A Johanson and Johanna Andersson, married to Birgitta Lundgren. Attended Västra Real School in Gothenburg, trade institution. Worked as a sales assistant for Frans Lundin in Gothenburg from 1910, and for Gulin, Weidenborg & Co from 1911 to 1915. Became director of his own company, AB Hagne, Weidenborg & Co in Gothenburg since its establishment in 1916. Weidenborg left the company in 1935, and his son Herbert Hagne joined as an employee in 1943. He served as a board member and treasurer in Från Gothenburg's Gentlemen's Apparel. Traveled to Norway, Denmark, England, Germany, and France from 1923 to 1932. Holds positions in the Association of Gothenburg Merchants and Traders, Gothenburg Coldin Association, Bowl Club No. 3 in Gothenburg, and other sports and recreational organizations. Hobbies: Sports, all kinds.
